        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>. <date>March. 7</date>. <add>Hebrew</add></p>
            <p>Rev. <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Rev. Sir and Friend</p>
            <p>Better later than never. Since my arrival<lb/> here I many times made up my mind<lb/> to
                write to you not only a note but<lb/> something for your magazine which however<lb/> I was
                always obliged to postpone&#8212;and thus<lb/> I delayed even writing you a few lines<lb/>
                concerning my self and my Cong<hi rend="sup">n</hi>.
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Without waiting until I have time<lb/> to finish something for your journal I pen<lb/> you
                these lines telling you that I thank<lb/> God feel happy in my present situation<lb/> being
                among respectable&#44; liberal<lb/> people and well respected by them.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">But the true satisfaction I enjoy<lb/> is the <sic>consiousnes</sic> of having been<lb/>
                instrument in producing a great<lb/> change for the better&#44; and a happy<lb/> improvement in
                religious matters<lb/> among our brethren here. Our<lb/> Synagogue which as every body<lb/>
                assert was almost deserted on a<lb/> Sabbath or holy day before my arrival<lb/> is now
                almost every Sabbath crowded to its utmost extent. Some</p>
            
            <p><add>Note&#58; The letter cuts off here.  A page or pages are missing.</add></p>


        </body>
